<doc id="857558" wikidata="Q2383560" url="?curid=857558" title="Danaphos">
<text>Danaphos is an oceanic ray-finned fish genus which belongs in the family Sternoptychidae. A common name is bottlelights.

==Species==
There are currently two recognized species in this genus:
* &quot;Danaphos asteroscopus&quot; 
* &quot;Danaphos oculatus&quot; (Bottlelights, Bigeye Lightfish)

Fossils of bottlelights show that the genus was already distinct in the Late Eocene, more than 35 million years ago.

