<doc id="857575" wikidata="Q15218534" url="?curid=857575" title="Maurolicus">
<text>Maurolicus is an oceanic ray-finned fish genus which belongs in the marine hatchetfish family Sternoptychidae. They are commonly known as pearlsides, but the brilliant pearlside is the related &quot;Argyripnus iridescens&quot;. Occasionally, &quot;bristle-mouth fishes&quot; is used as a common name, but that usually refers to the genus &quot;Argyripnus&quot; or the family Gonostomatidae.

Fossils of pearlsides are known from the Miocene.

==Species==
There are currently 15 recognized species in this genus:
* &quot;Maurolicus amethystinopunctatus&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus australis&quot; (pennant pearlside)
* &quot;Maurolicus breviculus&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus imperatorius&quot; (Emperor seamount lightfish)
* &quot;Maurolicus inventionis&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus japonicus&quot; (North Pacific lightfish)
* &quot;Maurolicus javanicus&quot; (Javan pearlside)
* &quot;Maurolicus kornilovorum&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus mucronatus&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus muelleri&quot; (Silvery lightfish, Mueller&#x27;s pearlside, Mueller&#x27;s bristle-mouth fish)
* &quot;Maurolicus parvipinnis&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus rudjakovi&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus stehmanni&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus walvisensis&quot; 
* &quot;Maurolicus weitzmani&quot; (Atlantic pearlside, Weitzman&#x27;s pearlside)

